******
[2] Orissa
Date: 27 May 2015
Source: The New Indian Express [edited]
http://www.newindianexpress.com/states/odisha/Doctors-Visit-Anthrax-hit-Village/2015/05/27/article2835375.ece


A team of health officials on Tuesday visited Kapadanga village under Sankarada gram panchayat of Kashipur block after 2 persons died of anthrax since 19 May 2015. 8 others from the village have been affected by the disease.

The deceased were aged 60 and 62 and died on 19 May and 23 May 2015, respectively. The health team was led by Dr Prasanna Kumar Mishra of Kashipur Hospital. He stated that consumption of raw beef might be the reason behind spread of the disease. The health team administered medicines to the affected.

