[For a map of India, go to: http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/middle_east_and_asia/india_physio-2001.jpg.
Tamil Nadu is in the far south of the country. Berhampur is in southern Odisha; see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brahmapur,_Odisha Odisha (once known as Orissa) is in the northeast and next to West Bengal.

Both states have severe anthrax problems. But it is a change to see the veterinary authorities in Tamil Nadu taking such a vigorous response to the threat from this dead elephant to protect the livestock in neighboring villages. - Mod MHJ]
